<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,332,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vondel" box="[343,504,332,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" refString="Vondel, B. J. van. (1991) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Haliplus subgenus Liaphlus Guignot (Coleoptera: Haliplidae). Tijdschrift Uoor Entomologie, 134, 75 - 144." type="journal article" year="1991">Vondel (1991)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that the records of 
<bibRefCitation author="Hosseinie" box="[846,1033,332,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" refString="Hosseinie, S. O. (1974) Water beetles found in the vicinity of Shiraz, Iran (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae, Noteridae, Haliplidae, Gyrinidae, and Hydrophilidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 28 (4), 237 - 243." type="journal article" year="1974">Hosseinie (1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hosseinie" box="[1046,1103,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" refString="Hosseinie, S. O. (1978) Aquatic Coleoptera from South-western Iran (Haliplidae, Dytiscidae and Gyrinidae, with a note on Hydrophilidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 32 (2), 167 - 176." type="journal article" year="1978">1978</bibRefCitation>
) might concern other species like 
<taxonomicName box="[201,368,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviatus">
<emphasis box="[201,368,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">H. abbreviatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the presence in Iran is now confirmed (Vondel: 
<tableCitation box="[975,1059,367,392]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,1334,1357]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,1417,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Examined material of Iranian Hydroscaphidae, Sphaeriusidae, Gyrinidae, Haliplidae, Noteridae and Rhysodidae." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/4F95665FE52BFFDDFF27901A426D4D7B" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" tableUuid="4F95665FE52BFFDDFF27901A426D4D7B">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Living in stagnant waterbodies with fresh water, often with a vegetation of Characeans, 
<taxonomicName box="[804,922,404,428]" class="Sphagnopsida" family="Sphagnaceae" genus="Sphagnum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sphagnales" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[804,922,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Sphagnum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[964,1059,405,428]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Hypnum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[964,1059,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Hypnum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in temporary dune-pools and in peat bogs (
<bibRefCitation author="Vondel" box="[276,426,439,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" refString="Vondel, B. J. van. (1997) Haliplidae. Susswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa, 20 (2), 1 - 95." type="journal article" year="1997">Vondel 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Also found in shallow, slow-moving streams (
<bibRefCitation author="Hosseinie" box="[976,1155,439,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" refString="Hosseinie, S. O. (1978) Aquatic Coleoptera from South-western Iran (Haliplidae, Dytiscidae and Gyrinidae, with a note on Hydrophilidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 32 (2), 167 - 176." type="journal article" year="1978">Hosseinie 1978</bibRefCitation>
) and remaining pools in riverbeds (
<bibRefCitation author="Hosseinie" box="[270,449,476,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" refString="Hosseinie, S. O. (1974) Water beetles found in the vicinity of Shiraz, Iran (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae, Noteridae, Haliplidae, Gyrinidae, and Hydrophilidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 28 (4), 237 - 243." type="journal article" year="1974">Hosseinie 1974</bibRefCitation>
). In rice fields (
<bibRefCitation author="Mousavi" box="[624,855,476,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" refString="Mousavi, A., Marjanyan, M. A. &amp; Kalashian, M. Yu. (2016) Contribution to the knowledge of the fauna of aquatic Adephaga (Coleoptera) of Mazadaran province of Iran (Families Haliplidae and Dytiscidae). Humanity space International almanac Vol. 5, Supplement 2, 2016, 18 - 21." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Mousavi 
<emphasis box="[731,780,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
